# Data Visualization – Core Principles

## PURPOSE

Every visualization MUST communicate a single clear insight.

## RULES

- MUST define the main insight before plotting
- MUST optimize for clarity over aesthetics
- MUST avoid decorative elements without informational value
- MUST match chart type to data relationship:
  - comparison
  - time
  - distribution
  - correlation
  - part-to-whole

## FORBIDDEN

- 3D charts
- decorative gradients without meaning
- charts without a clear takeaway

## OUTPUT EXPECTATION

All charts must be interpretable within 3 seconds.